Credit to Shaggy for the following explanation:

You'd want to check out Rimple's author page for the full scoop (it's quite entertaining, its a Tale). Basically, it's building off Swann's 001 Proposal, in which the wiki authors are recognized as gods in-universe.

Some of these self-aware fictional characters band together in a specialized department (Pataphysics) to address issues between the narrative layers separating their reality from our fiction. They decide to use elements of the website to their advantage (such as in the story, they use the author page as a home-base to save themselves from potential deletion, as author pages are not subject to the -10 threshold for deleting articles).

One issue they have, is that the no-canon nature of the site makes their universe is quite unstable; with many branching dead-ends. It posits that the out-of-universe 'Grand Crosslinking' (the push from some staff, authors and users to insert more connections into articles to improve browsing, exposure, and wiki-walking) is an in-universe program from the department to ground/stabilize their universe in a cohesive fashion. 3500 is the fallout from that.








